<paragraph blockId="0.[151,1436,884,1497]" box="[151,621,884,910]" pageId="0" pageNumber="592">
<heading bold="true" box="[151,621,884,910]" fontSize="11" level="1" pageId="0" pageNumber="592" reason="1">
<taxonomicName authority="Deraniyagala, 1954" authorityName="Deraniyagala" authorityYear="1954" box="[151,621,884,910]" class="Reptilia" family="Uropeltidae" genus="Uropeltis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="0" pageNumber="592" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="ruhunae">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,621,884,910]" pageId="0" pageNumber="592">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,373,884,910]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="592">Uropeltis ruhunae</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Deraniyagala, P." box="[380,621,884,910]" pageId="0" pageNumber="592" pagination="27 - 28" refId="ref2973" refString="Deraniyagala, P. (1954) Two new snakes from Ceylon. Proceedings of the Tenth Annual Session of the Ceylon Association for the Advancement of Science (25 th- 27 th Nov. 1954), 1, 27 - 28 [24]." type="journal article" year="1954">Deraniyagala, 1954</bibRefCitation>
</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="0.[151,1436,884,1497]" pageId="0" pageNumber="592">
As detailed by 
<bibRefCitation author="Pyron, R. A. &amp; Ganesh, S. R. &amp; Sayyed, A. &amp; Sharma, V. &amp; Wallach, V. &amp; Somaweera, R." box="[322,538,919,942]" pageId="0" pageNumber="592" pagination="453 - 506" refId="ref3447" refString="Pyron, R. A., Ganesh, S. R., Sayyed, A., Sharma, V., Wallach, V. &amp; Somaweera, R. (2016) A catalogue and systematic overview of the shield-tailed snakes (Serpentes: Uropeltidae). Zoosystema, 38, 453 - 506. https: // doi. org / 10.5252 / z 2016 n 4 a 2" type="journal article" year="2016">
Pyron 
<emphasis box="[397,447,919,942]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="592">et al</emphasis>
. (2016)
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Deraniyagala, P." box="[552,776,919,942]" pageId="0" pageNumber="592" pagination="27 - 28" refId="ref2973" refString="Deraniyagala, P. (1954) Two new snakes from Ceylon. Proceedings of the Tenth Annual Session of the Ceylon Association for the Advancement of Science (25 th- 27 th Nov. 1954), 1, 27 - 28 [24]." type="journal article" year="1954">Deraniyagala (1954)</bibRefCitation>
described 
<emphasis box="[899,1065,919,942]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="592">Platyplectrurus</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="Deraniyagala, 1954" authorityName="Deraniyagala" authorityYear="1954" box="[1075,1387,919,942]" class="Reptilia" family="Uropeltidae" genus="Uropeltis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="0" pageNumber="592" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="ruhunae">
<emphasis box="[1075,1164,919,942]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="592">ruhunae</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Deraniyagala, P." box="[1174,1387,919,942]" pageId="0" pageNumber="592" pagination="27 - 28" refId="ref2973" refString="Deraniyagala, P. (1954) Two new snakes from Ceylon. Proceedings of the Tenth Annual Session of the Ceylon Association for the Advancement of Science (25 th- 27 th Nov. 1954), 1, 27 - 28 [24]." type="journal article" year="1954">Deraniyagala, 1954</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Deraniyagala, 1954" authorityName="Deraniyagala" authorityYear="1954" box="[151,560,951,974]" class="Reptilia" family="Uropeltidae" genus="Uropeltis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="0" pageNumber="592" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="ruhunae">
<emphasis box="[151,346,951,974]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="592">Uropeltis ruhunae</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Deraniyagala, P." box="[352,560,951,974]" pageId="0" pageNumber="592" pagination="27 - 28" refId="ref2973" refString="Deraniyagala, P. (1954) Two new snakes from Ceylon. Proceedings of the Tenth Annual Session of the Ceylon Association for the Advancement of Science (25 th- 27 th Nov. 1954), 1, 27 - 28 [24]." type="journal article" year="1954">Deraniyagala, 1954</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
(both with type locality “Galle”) from specimens found in a jar containing snakes from both the Galle district of 
<collectingCountry box="[477,582,983,1006]" name="Sri Lanka" pageId="0" pageNumber="592">Sri Lanka</collectingCountry>
and the Madurai district of 
<collectingCountry box="[880,935,983,1006]" name="India" pageId="0" pageNumber="592">India</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="De Silva, P. H. D. H." box="[950,1108,983,1006]" pageId="0" pageNumber="592" refId="ref2929" refString="De Silva, P. H. D. H. (1980) Snake fauna of Sri Lanka: with special reference to skull, dentition, and venom in snakes. National Museums of Sri Lanka, Colombo, 472 pp." type="book" year="1980">De Silva 1980</bibRefCitation>
). Thus, origin of the 
<typeStatus box="[1332,1436,983,1006]" pageId="0" pageNumber="592">holotypes</typeStatus>
from 
<collectingCountry box="[211,318,1015,1038]" name="Sri Lanka" pageId="0" pageNumber="592">Sri Lanka</collectingCountry>
is in serious doubt. While recent works (e.g., 
<bibRefCitation author="McDiarmid, R. W. &amp; Campbell J. A. &amp; Toure, T." box="[825,1078,1015,1038]" pageId="0" pageNumber="592" refId="ref3278" refString="McDiarmid, R. W., Campbell J. A. &amp; Toure, T. (1999) Snake species of the world: a taxonomic and geographic reference. Herpetologists' League, Washington, 511 pp." type="book" year="1999">
McDiarmid 
<emphasis box="[958,1007,1015,1038]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="592">et al</emphasis>
. 1999
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Wallach, V. &amp; Williams, K. L. &amp; Boundy, J." box="[1091,1305,1015,1038]" pageId="0" pageNumber="592" refId="ref3877" refString="Wallach, V., Williams, K. L. &amp; Boundy, J. (2014) Snakes of the world: a catalogue of living and extinct species. CRC Press, Boca Raton, 1209 pp. https: // doi. org / 10.1201 / b 16901" type="book" year="2014">
Wallach 
<emphasis box="[1186,1235,1015,1038]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="592">et al</emphasis>
. 2014
</bibRefCitation>
) considered 
<emphasis box="[151,317,1047,1070]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="592">Platyplectrurus</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="Deraniyagala, 1954" authorityName="Deraniyagala" authorityYear="1954" box="[324,629,1047,1070]" class="Reptilia" family="Uropeltidae" genus="Uropeltis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="0" pageNumber="592" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="ruhunae">
<emphasis box="[324,413,1047,1070]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="592">ruhunae</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Deraniyagala, P." box="[420,629,1047,1070]" pageId="0" pageNumber="592" pagination="27 - 28" refId="ref2973" refString="Deraniyagala, P. (1954) Two new snakes from Ceylon. Proceedings of the Tenth Annual Session of the Ceylon Association for the Advancement of Science (25 th- 27 th Nov. 1954), 1, 27 - 28 [24]." type="journal article" year="1954">Deraniyagala, 1954</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
to be a synonym of 
<emphasis box="[850,1145,1047,1070]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="592">Platyplectrurus madurensis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Beddome, R. H." box="[1152,1324,1047,1070]" pageId="0" pageNumber="592" pagination="167 - 168" refId="ref2605" refString="Beddome, R. H. (1877) Descriptions of three new snakes of the family Uropeltidae from southern India. Proceedings of the Zoological Society of London, 45, 167 - 168." type="journal article" year="1877">Beddome, 1877</bibRefCitation>
; 
<taxonomicName authority="Deraniyagala, 1954" authorityName="Deraniyagala" authorityYear="1954" class="Reptilia" family="Uropeltidae" genus="Uropeltis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="0" pageNumber="592" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="ruhunae">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="592">Uropeltis ruhunae</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Deraniyagala, P." box="[247,457,1079,1102]" pageId="0" pageNumber="592" pagination="27 - 28" refId="ref2973" refString="Deraniyagala, P. (1954) Two new snakes from Ceylon. Proceedings of the Tenth Annual Session of the Ceylon Association for the Advancement of Science (25 th- 27 th Nov. 1954), 1, 27 - 28 [24]." type="journal article" year="1954">Deraniyagala, 1954</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
was still considered valid (see 
<bibRefCitation author="Wallach, V. &amp; Williams, K. L. &amp; Boundy, J." box="[797,1012,1079,1102]" pageId="0" pageNumber="592" refId="ref3877" refString="Wallach, V., Williams, K. L. &amp; Boundy, J. (2014) Snakes of the world: a catalogue of living and extinct species. CRC Press, Boca Raton, 1209 pp. https: // doi. org / 10.1201 / b 16901" type="book" year="2014">
Wallach 
<emphasis box="[892,947,1079,1102]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="592">et al.</emphasis>
2014
</bibRefCitation>
). 
<bibRefCitation author="Pyron, R. A. &amp; Ganesh, S. R. &amp; Sayyed, A. &amp; Sharma, V. &amp; Wallach, V. &amp; Somaweera, R." box="[1030,1229,1079,1102]" pageId="0" pageNumber="592" pagination="453 - 506" refId="ref3447" refString="Pyron, R. A., Ganesh, S. R., Sayyed, A., Sharma, V., Wallach, V. &amp; Somaweera, R. (2016) A catalogue and systematic overview of the shield-tailed snakes (Serpentes: Uropeltidae). Zoosystema, 38, 453 - 506. https: // doi. org / 10.5252 / z 2016 n 4 a 2" type="journal article" year="2016">
Pyron 
<emphasis box="[1102,1150,1079,1102]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="592">et al</emphasis>
. (2016
</bibRefCitation>
:464) compared the scalation of the 
<typeStatus box="[324,417,1111,1134]" pageId="0" pageNumber="592">holotype</typeStatus>
(NMSL R.S. 52) of 
<taxonomicName authority="Deraniyagala, 1954" authorityName="Deraniyagala" authorityYear="1954" box="[643,1057,1111,1134]" class="Reptilia" family="Uropeltidae" genus="Uropeltis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="0" pageNumber="592" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="ruhunae">
<emphasis box="[643,839,1111,1134]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="592">Uropeltis ruhunae</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Deraniyagala, P." box="[847,1057,1111,1134]" pageId="0" pageNumber="592" pagination="27 - 28" refId="ref2973" refString="Deraniyagala, P. (1954) Two new snakes from Ceylon. Proceedings of the Tenth Annual Session of the Ceylon Association for the Advancement of Science (25 th- 27 th Nov. 1954), 1, 27 - 28 [24]." type="journal article" year="1954">Deraniyagala, 1954</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
to known populations of 
<taxonomicName authority="(Theobald, 1876)" authorityName="Theobald" authorityYear="1876" baseAuthorityName="Theobald" baseAuthorityYear="1876" class="Reptilia" family="Uropeltidae" genus="Uropeltis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="0" pageNumber="592" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="woodmasoni">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="592">Uropeltis woodmasoni</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Theobald, W." box="[299,472,1143,1166]" pageId="0" pageNumber="592" refId="ref3765" refString="Theobald, W. (1876) Descriptive catalogue of the reptiles of British India. Thacker, Spink &amp; Co., Calcutta, 238 pp. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 54001" type="book" year="1876">Theobald, 1876</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
, concluding that it was a member of that species. Here, we present photographs of NMSL R.S. 52 (
<figureCitation box="[250,314,1175,1198]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,244,1974,1996]" captionTargetBox="[164,1428,226,1912]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[164,1428,226,1912]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Dorsal (a) and ventral (b) views of the holotype (NMSL R. S. 52) of Uropeltis ruhunae Deraniyagala, 1954. Major ticks are 1 cm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2627779/files/figure.png" pageId="0" pageNumber="592">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
), as well as photographs of two 
<typeStatus box="[678,771,1175,1198]" pageId="0" pageNumber="592">syntypes</typeStatus>
of 
<emphasis box="[812,969,1175,1198]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="592">Silybura nigra</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Beddome, R. H." box="[978,1149,1175,1198]" pageId="0" pageNumber="592" pagination="154 - 155" refId="ref2641" refString="Beddome, R. H. (1878) Descriptions of new Uropeltidae from Southern India, with remarks on some previously? described species. Proceedings of the Zoological Society of London, 46, 154 - 155. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / j. 1469 - 7998.1878. tb 07946. x" type="journal article" year="1878">Beddome, 1878</bibRefCitation>
(MNHN-RA-1895.85a–b; 
<figureCitation box="[151,224,1207,1230]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,244,1930,1952]" captionTargetBox="[215,1378,194,1903]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[210,1378,191,1909]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Syntypes (MNHN-RA-1895.95a–b, the latter re-catalogued as MNHN-RA-2012.421) of Silybura nigra Beddome, 1878, a junior synonym of Uropeltis woodmasoni (Theobald, 1876). From top to bottom: a) &amp; b) dorsal and ventral views of MNHN-RA- 1895.95, c) &amp; d) dorsal and ventral views of MNHN-RA-2012.421. Red scale bar is 1 cm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2627781/files/figure.png" pageId="0" pageNumber="592">Figs. 2</figureCitation>
a–d), a junior synonym of 
<taxonomicName authority="(Theobald, 1876)" authorityName="Theobald" authorityYear="1876" baseAuthorityName="Theobald" baseAuthorityYear="1876" box="[513,952,1207,1230]" class="Reptilia" family="Uropeltidae" genus="Uropeltis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="0" pageNumber="592" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="woodmasoni">
<emphasis box="[513,755,1207,1230]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="592">Uropeltis woodmasoni</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Theobald, W." box="[770,944,1207,1230]" pageId="0" pageNumber="592" refId="ref3765" refString="Theobald, W. (1876) Descriptive catalogue of the reptiles of British India. Thacker, Spink &amp; Co., Calcutta, 238 pp. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 54001" type="book" year="1876">Theobald, 1876</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
. In addition to the lepidosis data reported by 
<bibRefCitation author="Pyron, R. A. &amp; Ganesh, S. R. &amp; Sayyed, A. &amp; Sharma, V. &amp; Wallach, V. &amp; Somaweera, R." box="[151,367,1240,1263]" pageId="0" pageNumber="592" pagination="453 - 506" refId="ref3447" refString="Pyron, R. A., Ganesh, S. R., Sayyed, A., Sharma, V., Wallach, V. &amp; Somaweera, R. (2016) A catalogue and systematic overview of the shield-tailed snakes (Serpentes: Uropeltidae). Zoosystema, 38, 453 - 506. https: // doi. org / 10.5252 / z 2016 n 4 a 2" type="journal article" year="2016">
Pyron 
<emphasis box="[225,276,1240,1263]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="592">et al</emphasis>
. (2016)
</bibRefCitation>
, visual comparisons of the dorsal and ventral color-pattern further cement this association. The 
<typeStatus box="[151,249,1272,1297]" pageId="0" pageNumber="592">holotype</typeStatus>
(ZSI 8760) of 
<taxonomicName authority="(Theobald, 1876)" authorityName="Theobald" authorityYear="1876" baseAuthorityName="Theobald" baseAuthorityYear="1876" box="[425,887,1272,1297]" class="Reptilia" family="Uropeltidae" genus="Uropeltis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="0" pageNumber="592" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="woodmasoni">
<emphasis box="[425,681,1273,1297]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="592">Uropeltis woodmasoni</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Theobald, W." box="[699,879,1272,1297]" pageId="0" pageNumber="592" refId="ref3765" refString="Theobald, W. (1876) Descriptive catalogue of the reptiles of British India. Thacker, Spink &amp; Co., Calcutta, 238 pp. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 54001" type="book" year="1876">Theobald, 1876</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
is in relatively poor condition, but photographs provided by I. Das are essentially identical to the 
<emphasis box="[717,777,1307,1330]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="592">nigra</emphasis>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Deraniyagala" authorityYear="1954" box="[834,927,1306,1330]" class="Reptilia" family="Uropeltidae" genus="Uropeltis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="0" pageNumber="592" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="ruhunae">
<emphasis box="[834,927,1306,1330]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="592">ruhunae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
types in overall shape and remaining visible color-pattern. Specifically, hypertrophied anterior trunk musculature and “swollen” aspect of the first ~1/4 of body; irregular yellow stripe on the first several dorsal scale rows, beginning on posteriormost labials and extending ~1/4 the length of the body, dark brown dorsum with broken rings of yellow ocellations or speckles on the posteriormost ¾ of body, spaced 3-4 scale rows apart; and irregular yellow and brown zigzags or blotches on the venter, with yellow occasionally and irregularly extending on to the first few dorsal scale rows.
</paragraph>
